# Manual HTTP probes for the categories module (Phase 4 / Slice 5).
#
# How to use:
#   1. Start the server with `task run`.
#   2. Open this file in JetBrains GoLand/IntelliJ or VSCode with the
#      REST Client extension installed.
#   3. Click the gutter icon next to a request to send it.
#
# Substitute <categoryId> after POST /categories returns one (or look
# it up via `psql` against the dev database).

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### POST {{baseUrl}}/categories — create a new category
POST {{baseUrl}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Fiction"
}

### GET {{baseUrl}}/categories?startsWith=fi — list categories whose name starts with "fi"
GET {{baseUrl}}/categories?startsWith=fi

### GET {{baseUrl}}/categories/<categoryId> — read a single category
GET {{baseUrl}}/categories/<categoryId>
